<calisher@cybersafe.net>

[The earlier report on an outbreak of flavivirus infections and deaths in
Cordoba, Argentina, was confirmed as caused by SLEV, instead of West Nile
virus, according to a reliable source. Further information regarding what
other animals and birds were affected and the rate of infection among
mosquitoes in the affected areas will be helpful in terms of outbreak
control and prevention measures. - Mod.RY]
